This page explains how to make a CatVPy question for your own CAT-SOOP course.

<catsoop-section>Install CAT-SOOP</catsoop-section>
Follow the instructions at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://catsoop.org/docs/installing">https://catsoop.org/docs/installing</a> to install CAT-SOOP.

<catsoop-section>Install VPython</catsoop-section>
Follow the instructions at <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://pypi.org/project/vpython/">https://pypi.org/project/vpython</a> to install VPython.

<catsoop-section>Install the Question Type</catsoop-section>
Add the `__QTYPES__/vpython/vpython.py` file to your course.

For a quick start, clone <a target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://github.com/aherrera1721/catvpy">the CatVPy course</a>.
